I gave my wife, a child abuse social worker veteran, my last post to read. She responded: &quot;what about the children, those that had American fathers? The bastards of the war? They are rejected by the Vietnamese, abandoned by their fathers, and are the lowest of the low.  Are not these the real victims of the war? Second class citizens at best? Are they Vietnamese because their mothers are, or just the crap of the country? They are the REAL victims. Now they are adults. What will happen to their offspring?  They have more &quot;americanized eyes&quot; and lighter skin, and, god forbid, freckles. They will never be accepted. Where are they, and there children now?  Where are they, the product of American G.I.'s who just wanted to get laid?<br><br>
KAPOW, (to quote Arthur), that is my wife's question, and I wrote it as she dictated it.  Well Viet Son, and my veteran comrades, what about what she said?<br><br>
